ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: How critical is (relative) of you?
Notes: 1= Not at all critical; 10= Very critical indeed

ElementDescription: How warm is (relative) towards you?
Notes: 1= Not at all warm; 10= Very warm indeed

ElementDescription: How disaproving is (relative) of what you do?
Notes: 1= Not at all disapproving; 10= Very disapproving indeed

ElementDescription: How caring is (relative) of you?
Notes: 1= Not at all caring; 10= Very caring indeed

ElementDescription: How much do the things you do annoy (relative)?
Notes: 1= Not at all; 10= Very much indeed

ElementDescription: How much does (relative) like to spend time and do things with you?
Notes: 1= Does not like it at all; 10= Likes it very much indeed

ElementDescription: Do you feel criticized by (relative)?
Notes: 1= Not criticized at all; 10= Very criticized indeed

ElementDescription: Do you feel loved by (relative)?
Notes: 1= Not loved at all; 10= Very loved indeed
